frameDefinitions: A Timetable of Events is a mental object deliberately created, modified or kept by a Cognizer.
A Guest stays for a time at a Location, which is not his or her permanent residence, for some Duration.
This frame has similarities to Experiencer_subject, but here the verbs are more 'active' in meaning.
An Agent schedules an Event to take place at a specified Scheduled_time and Place.
Words in the frame refer to any Document that has a legal status or conventional social significance.
The word(s) in this frame detail a particular moment in time.
frameExamples: Changes to an employee's work <t><fex name='tt'>schedule</fex></t> should generally be approved prior to the change actually occuring.
I usually <t>stay</t> with my aunt at her summer house when I go to Seville.
Pat is still <t>worrying</t> about the exam.
Gina <t>scheduled</t> a dentist appointment for Monday in Berkeley.
They got their marriage <t>licence</t> from Canada.
listRoleDefinitions: The mental schedule of times at which the <fen>Events</fen> are set to take place.
The events which are to take place at specified times acording to the <fen>Timetable</fen>.
The sentient entity who keeps the <fen>Timetable</fen>.
The <fen>Guest</fen> remains for a relatively short period of time in the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Location</fen> where the <fen>Guest</fen> spends a short amount of time.
The length of time that the <fen>Guest</fen> remains at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Host</fen> is living at the <fen>Location</fen> on a permanent basis, and is allowing the <fen>Guest</fen> to stay there.
The time at which the temporary stay takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates the larger physical setting of the temporary stay.
The role <fen>Experiencer</fen> indicates the one who is actively expressing emotion over the <fen>Topic</fen>.  It usually occurs as the subject of the verb.
The Experiencer's emotion generally is about something.  This is indicated with a <fen>Topic</fen> which usually occurs in a PP-Complement.
The sentient being who schedules an <fen>Event</fen> to take place at a <fen>Time</fen> and <fen>Place</fen>.
The incident that the <fen>Agent</fen> has scheduled to take place at a <fen>Time</fen> and <fen>Place</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Event</fen> is scheduled to take place.
This role describes the time at which the scheduling occurs.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> has scheduled the <fen>Event</fen> to take place.
The holder of the document.
The authority that issues the document.
Obligation is the obligation that is imposed on the <fen>Bearer</fen> of the <fen>Document</fen>.
Right is the right of the <fen>Bearer</fen> of the <fen>Document</fen>  that is authorized by the <fen>Document</fen>.
Status is the state of the Bearer of the Document indicated by the Document.
Document is the piece of paper that has the legal status.

The particular, salient point in time. If a specified time is present, it is the focal time. Otherwise, the unit is the focal time. If there is an appositive that specifies an entity that it not necessarily larger than the target, both the unit and the specification are the FE.
listRoleExamples: My idiot friend forgot his class <fex>schedule</fex> again.
What's your <fex>class</fex> schedule like this spring?
<fex>John's</fex> schedule is packed this afternoon.
Originally, <fex>we</fex> planned on rooming with our relatives in Reno.
Originally we planned on staying <fex>at the Hilton</fex>.
My wife and have just returned from a <fex>two day</fex> stay at Ocean Key.
You should avoid staying <fex>with old college buddies</fex> when on business trips.
He'll be lodging here <fex>next month</fex>.
<fex>In London</fex>, I stayed at a hotel.
<fex>Kim</fex> worried about the phone bill.
Kim fretted <fex>over the exam</fex>.
<fex>I</fex> set up a meeting with Carlos on Monday.
I'd like to set up <fex>a meeting with Mr. Hofmann</fex>.
Maria scheduled the appointment <fex>for Monday</fex>.
Gina scheduled a dentist appointment for Monday <fex>in Berkeley</fex>.
<fex>My </fex> visa will expire next month.
<fex>US consulate</fex> issued a Visa to Ms. Yang to travel to San Francisco.
They were all under subpoena <fex>to appear in court.</fex>
Raymond has a <fex>fishing</fex> licence.
The couple just got their <fex>marriage</fex> certificate.
The police need a search <fex><t>warrant</t></fex> to enter his house.
